<item>
            <title>[TIKA-3023] Text files starting with MOVI are detected as X-SGI-Movie</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/TIKA-3023</link>
                <project id="12310631" key="TIKA">Tika</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;If a plaintext file starts with &quot;MOVI&quot; Tika labels it as an SGI Movie.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The hex conversion for MOVI is 4D 4F 56 49 which is the same as the header for the SGI Movie file format&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://reposcope.com/mimetype/video/x-sgi-movie&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://reposcope.com/mimetype/video/x-sgi-movie&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&#160;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This SGI format isn&apos;t supported so any information from a text file starting like this would be lost. I&apos;ve attached a simple file that should recreate the problem.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment>&lt;p&gt;Issue recreated on&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Windows 10 Professional 64bit running the runnable Jar&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Ubuntu 16.04.6 LTS running Tika-Python&lt;/p&gt;</environment>
