                            <comment id="17010968" author="tallison@mitre.org" created="Wed, 8 Jan 2020 19:46:10 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I regret that I know nothing about this format.&#160;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;TRID requires only &quot;MOVI&quot;:&#160;&lt;a href=&quot;http://file-extension.net/seeker/file_extension_SGI&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://file-extension.net/seeker/file_extension_SGI&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I couldn&apos;t quickly find a signature in Pronom.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;tt&gt;file&lt;/tt&gt; requires only &quot;MOVI&quot;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&#160;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;From the files linked here:&#160;&lt;a href=&quot;http://fileformats.archiveteam.org/wiki/SGI_movie&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://fileformats.archiveteam.org/wiki/SGI_movie&lt;/a&gt;, it looks like they all start with &quot;MOVI\u0000&quot;.&#160;&#160;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&#160;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Any objections to adding a 0x00 after MOVI?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17011634" author="gagravarr" created="Thu, 9 Jan 2020 10:01:26 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Assuming that the byte after MOVI is part of a version or length field, perhaps safest to check for 0x00 or 0x01 or 0x02? That shouldn&apos;t trigger on text, but probably would help with the detection of the real thing. (Some sort of &quot;not a printable ascii field&quot; is probably a step too far and probably wouldn&apos;t help much either!)&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17031507" author="gagravarr" created="Thu, 6 Feb 2020 11:44:48 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;The FFMpeg project have some sample SGI Movie files at &lt;a href=&quot;https://samples.ffmpeg.org/sgi/&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://samples.ffmpeg.org/sgi/&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Based on looking at a few, I think MOVI followed by a very low or high byte ought to be a safe check. I&apos;ve added that in &lt;tt&gt;0d259bc8b&lt;/tt&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17031579" author="hudson" created="Thu, 6 Feb 2020 13:20:25 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;SUCCESS: Integrated in Jenkins build Tika-trunk #1769 (See &lt;a href=&quot;https://builds.apache.org/job/Tika-trunk/1769/&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://builds.apache.org/job/Tika-trunk/1769/&lt;/a&gt;)&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/TIKA-3023&quot; title=&quot;Text files starting with MOVI are detected as X-SGI-Movie&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;TIKA-3023&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;TIKA-3023&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; Make the SGI Movie mime magic more specific to avoid false (nick: &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/tika/commit/0d259bc8b6beccaa9bac2e85212b57a48f171e83&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://github.com/apache/tika/commit/0d259bc8b6beccaa9bac2e85212b57a48f171e83&lt;/a&gt;)&lt;/p&gt;
